The paper deals with a wireless communication system using massive MIMO technology, which falls under the Information Theory (cs.IT) and Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI) categories. The paper also discusses the performance of the system, which involves analyzing and optimizing the system, making it relevant to the Systems and Control (cs.SY) category. The use of beamforming techniques and channel state information also makes it relevant to the Multimedia (cs.MM) category. Finally, the paper deals with the practical implementation of the system, which falls under the Computer Communications (cs.COM) category.
